<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 06 at 2:06AM MST  by NWS Pueblo</headline>
<description>...Light to Moderate Snow This Morning...
Light, to briefly moderate, snow will likely continue across the
Palmer Divide through around 6 AM MST this morning. Under the
heaviest snow, visibility will be reduced to one half mile, and
with roads becoming snow covered. Those traveling this morning,
especially along I-25 and Highway 24 in northern El Paso County,
should be prepared for hazardous driving conditions.</description>
